<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="seat-vt">seat <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /siːt/    美 /siːt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>使坐下；使就座：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>seated himself</strong> in a chair. 
他坐在椅子上。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He seated us in the front row. 
他安排我们在前排就座。</p></div>

<h3 id="seat-sit">辨析 seat, sit</h3>
<p><strong>seat ** 为及物动词，意为“使坐下”，“使就座”。
</strong>sit ** 为不及物动词，意为“坐下”。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Jean sat at the table writing a letter. 
琼坐在桌旁写信。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>供给...座位；容纳...人：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The hall was so large it could easily seat 6,000 people for dinner. 
大厅很宽敞，可以轻松容纳6000人用餐。</p><footer>北师大③ – 8</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-seated">be seated</h3>
<p>1.<strong>就座；坐下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Be seated, please. 
请坐。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Ladies and gentlemen, please remain <strong><em>_</em></strong>___ (seat) until the plane has come to a complete stop.   （2009 四川改）  </li>
<li>— Can those <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ (seat) at the back of the classroom hear me?
— No problem.   （2008 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. seated   2. seated  </p></div>